  "prompt": "Where can I learn Hadoop online for free?",
  "response": "Learning Hadoop online for free is possible through a variety of resources, including tutorials, documentation, and open online courses. Here are some of the best places to start learning Hadoop without spending money:\n\n1. **Apache Hadoop Official Documentation**: The official documentation is always the most accurate and comprehensive resource to learn Hadoop. It covers all the components of the Hadoop ecosystem in detail. You can find it at [Apache Hadoop's official website](https://hadoop.apache.org/).\n\n2. **YouTube**: There are numerous channels that offer free tutorials on Hadoop. Simply searching for \"Hadoop tutorials\" on YouTube should provide you with a variety of video series that range from beginner to advanced levels.\n\n3. **Khan Academy**: While Khan Academy doesn't have specific Hadoop content, it offers foundational courses in computer science and data analysis that can be beneficial for understanding the context in which Hadoop is used.\n\n4. **Coursera**: Some courses on Coursera offer free access to their content if you don't require a certificate. You can audit courses like \"Big Data\" from the University of California, San Diego, or \"Hadoop Platform and Application Framework\" from the University of California, San Diego.\n\n5. **edX**: Similar to Coursera, edX offers free courses in big data and Hadoop. For example, you can check out the \"Introduction to Big Data\" course from the University of Adelaide.\n\n6. **TutorialsPoint**: TutorialsPoint offers a comprehensive Hadoop tutorial that is available for free. It covers the basics of Hadoop and its ecosystem components like HDFS, YARN, MapReduce, and others.\n\n7. **Guru99**: Guru99 provides free tutorials on Hadoop with simple explanations and examples. It's a great resource for beginners.\n\n8. **MIT OpenCourseWare**: MIT offers a wealth of free courses and materials, including those that cover big data and related technologies.\n\n9. **Google Cloud Training**: Google Cloud offers free training on big data and machine learning, which can include components that are similar to or compatible with Hadoop technologies.\n\n10. **Big Data University**: Big Data University (now part of Cognitive Class AI) offers free courses on big data and Hadoop. They provide hands-on labs and exercises to practice what you learn.\n\nRemember that while the courses may be free, some platforms might charge for a certificate or for additional services. Always check the details of the course to understand what is included in the free offering. Additionally, the field is constantly evolving, so it's important to ensure that the resources you use are up-to-date with the latest versions and best practices.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
